            <thetext>The &#39;tap&#39; gesture is more or less the replacement for the &#39;click&#39; event. At least many applications will proceed like this.

To be able to easily migrate to a &#39;pointer events&#39; based solution the &#39;tap&#39; gesture should be equipped with the information a &#39;mouseup&#39; event would have.

This includes direct access to the

- getDocumentLeft
- getDocumentTop
- getViewportLeft
- getViewportTop
- getScreenLeft
- getScreenTop

methods directly at the event instance.</thetext>
